<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,303,1755,1781]" box="[189,303,1755,1781]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1755,1781]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1755,1781]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1399,1802,1899]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
This species is known as a gall-stem wasp of 
<emphasis box="[752,1278,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName box="[752,1004,1802,1828]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Phragmites" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="australis">Phragmites australis</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Erdos" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[1019,1278,1802,1828]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Tetramesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phragmitis">Tetramesa phragmitis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is widely distributed in the Palaearctic region from Europe to 
<collectingCountry box="[815,882,1838,1864]" name="Japan" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Boucek Z." box="[899,1062,1837,1863]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="231 - 260" refId="ref11041" refString="Boucek Z. 1968. Contributions to the Czechoslovak fauna of Chalcidoidea (Hym.). Acta Faunistica Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 12: 231 - 260." type="journal article" year="1968">Bouček 1968</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zerova M. D." box="[1076,1230,1837,1864]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="328 - 358" refId="ref12700" refString="Zerova M. D. 1978. Hymenoptera II. Chalcidoidea 8. Eurytomidae. Opredeliteli Nasekomykh Evropeyskoy Chasti SSR 3: 328 - 358." type="journal article" year="1978">Zerova 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kalina, V." box="[1244,1394,1837,1863]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="97 - 127" refId="ref11799" refString="Kalina, V. 1989. Checklist of Czechoslovak Insects III (Hymenoptera). Chalcidoidea. Acta Faunistica Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 19: 97 - 127." type="journal article" year="1989">Kalina 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zerova M. D. &amp; Fursov V. N." box="[189,462,1872,1899]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="85 - 88" refId="ref12768" refString="Zerova M. D. &amp; Fursov V. N. 2016. Redescription and new data on the distribution of Tetramesa phragmitis (Hymenoptera, Eurytomidae). Vestnik Zoologii 50 (1): 85 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.1515 / vzoo- 2016 - 0010" type="journal article" year="2016">Zerova &amp; Fursov 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1398,1937,2000]" lastBlockId="14.[189,1399,267,470]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
This species has recently been redescribed (
<bibRefCitation author="Zerova M. D. &amp; Fursov V. N." box="[728,1013,1937,1964]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="85 - 88" refId="ref12768" refString="Zerova M. D. &amp; Fursov V. N. 2016. Redescription and new data on the distribution of Tetramesa phragmitis (Hymenoptera, Eurytomidae). Vestnik Zoologii 50 (1): 85 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.1515 / vzoo- 2016 - 0010" type="journal article" year="2016">Zerova &amp; Fursov 2016</bibRefCitation>
) and our specimens exhibit the following variations: body larger, 
<quantity box="[611,683,1973,2000]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
(vs 
<quantity box="[741,888,1973,1999]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.3" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.3" valueMin="2.7">2.7–4.3 mm</quantity>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Zerova M. D. &amp; Fursov V. N." box="[933,1220,1973,2000]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="85 - 88" refId="ref12768" refString="Zerova M. D. &amp; Fursov V. N. 2016. Redescription and new data on the distribution of Tetramesa phragmitis (Hymenoptera, Eurytomidae). Vestnik Zoologii 50 (1): 85 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.1515 / vzoo- 2016 - 0010" type="journal article" year="2016">Zerova &amp; Fursov 2016</bibRefCitation>
), mainly dark, with yellow spots reduced to head, below eyes and lower face (
<figureCitation box="[961,1091,267,294]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1950,1976]" captionTargetBox="[237,1371,623,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[237,1371,623,1907]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 9. Tetramesa phragmitis (Erdös, 1952). A. Female in lateral view. B. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Fore wing. D. Propodeum in dorsal view. E. Head in frontal view. F. Antenna of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011142" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011142/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 9A, E</figureCitation>
) vs yellow spots on head and thorax, also much lighter specimens occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[785,852,302,328]" name="Israel" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Israel</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[909,1027,302,328]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zerova M. D. &amp; Fursov V. N." box="[1043,1324,302,329]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="85 - 88" refId="ref12768" refString="Zerova M. D. &amp; Fursov V. N. 2016. Redescription and new data on the distribution of Tetramesa phragmitis (Hymenoptera, Eurytomidae). Vestnik Zoologii 50 (1): 85 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.1515 / vzoo- 2016 - 0010" type="journal article" year="2016">Zerova &amp; Fursov 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Fore wing (
<figureCitation box="[265,357,338,364]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1950,1976]" captionTargetBox="[237,1371,623,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[237,1371,623,1907]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 9. Tetramesa phragmitis (Erdös, 1952). A. Female in lateral view. B. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Fore wing. D. Propodeum in dorsal view. E. Head in frontal view. F. Antenna of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011142" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011142/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
) mainly infuscate with two distinct dark spots, the first one under marginal and stigmal veins and the second as a V-shaped dark spot below submarginal vein vs unclear yellow spot under marginal vein (
<bibRefCitation author="Zerova M. D. &amp; Fursov V. N." box="[367,645,408,435]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="85 - 88" refId="ref12768" refString="Zerova M. D. &amp; Fursov V. N. 2016. Redescription and new data on the distribution of Tetramesa phragmitis (Hymenoptera, Eurytomidae). Vestnik Zoologii 50 (1): 85 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.1515 / vzoo- 2016 - 0010" type="journal article" year="2016">Zerova &amp; Fursov 2016</bibRefCitation>
); and distinctly dark-brown veins vs yellowish veins (
<bibRefCitation author="Zerova M. D. &amp; Fursov V. N." pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="85 - 88" refId="ref12768" refString="Zerova M. D. &amp; Fursov V. N. 2016. Redescription and new data on the distribution of Tetramesa phragmitis (Hymenoptera, Eurytomidae). Vestnik Zoologii 50 (1): 85 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.1515 / vzoo- 2016 - 0010" type="journal article" year="2016">Zerova &amp; Fursov 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
